{"parentUuid":"aad94cb1-46dd-41fe-bdf4-f36a78d95732","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DLwSwuuPXmPJygzTjf9AEJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the skills that question blind spots, interview you, and surface things you might be missing:\n\n**Direct Interview / Questioning Skills:**\n- **grill-me** — Interviews you about something, probing for gaps\n- **ask-questions-if-underspecified** — Clarifies requirements by asking what's missing before proceeding\n- **first-ask** — Interactive, input-to-output gathering (asks before acting)\n- **qa** — Interactive QA session to stress-test your thinking\n\n**Verification / Blind Spot Detection:**\n- **doublecheck** — Three-layer verification (catches things you assumed were fine)\n- **verification-before-completion** — Checks assumptions before claiming done\n- **fp-check** — Systematically verifies findings to eliminate false positives\n- **second-opinion** — Runs external LLM code review for an independent perspective\n\n**Risk / Threat Surfacing:**\n- **risk-assessment** — Identify, assess, and surface risks you may not have considered\n- **threat-model-analyst** — Full STRIDE-A threat model (security blind spots)\n- **sharp-edges** — Identifies error-prone patterns in code that could bite you later\n- **find-bugs** — Finds bugs and security vulnerabilities you may have missed\n\n**Strategic Blind Spots:**\n- **brainstorming** — Forces ideation before action (prevents tunnel vision)\n- **dogfood** — Systematically explores your own product to find UX/logic gaps\n- **noob-mode** — Plain-English translation — helps you see what's obvious to experts but invisible to users\n\n**Most relevant to your ask** (things a human is potentially unaware of):\n1. **grill-me** — actively interrogates you\n2. **doublecheck** — triple-checks your work\n3. **risk-assessment** — surfaces hidden risks\n4. **sharp-edges** — finds footguns in code\n5. **brainstorming** — prevents premature narrowing\n\nWant me to run any of these on something specific?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":34003,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":937,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":34003,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZZAqZD44EhiwXJKrPjpC","type":"assistant","uuid":"e978421e-1bf0-4ed6-adf2-50472687cb6c","timestamp":"2026-03-30T11:17:00.954Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/shunkakinoki/dotfiles","sessionId":"fedc713a-0e3e-46fa-8e3c-05fabfcb25c7","version":"2.1.87","gitBranch":"feat/codex-hooks"}
